import React, { useEffect, useRef, useState } from 'react'; import './web.css'; function Web() { const textRef = useRef(null); const [phraseIndex, setPhraseIndex] = useState(0); const [letterIndex, setLetterIndex] = useState(0); const phrases = [ "Welcome to my portfolio.", "I'm a software developer.", "Let's build something amazing!" ]; useEffect(() => { let typingInterval; const typeText = () => { typingInterval = setInterval(() => { if (letterIndex < phrases[phraseIndex].length) { textRef.current.textContent += phrases[phraseIndex].charAt(letterIndex); setLetterIndex(prev => prev + 1); } else { clearInterval(typingInterval); setTimeout(() => { eraseText(); }, 2000); // Wait before erasing } }, 100); }; const eraseText = () => { const eraseInterval = setInterval(() => { if (letterIndex > 0) { textRef.current.textContent = textRef.current.textContent.slice(0, -1); setLetterIndex(prev => prev - 1); } else { clearInterval(eraseInterval); setPhraseIndex(prev => (prev + 1) % phrases.length); setTimeout(() => { typeText(); }, 500); } }, 50); }; typeText(); // Start typing when component mounts return () => clearInterval(typingInterval); // Cleanup on component unmount }, [phraseIndex, letterIndex, phrases]); return ( <>
